 \tan(2\alpha) = \frac{2\tan\alpha}{1-\tan^2\alpha}. 
 \frac{8x}{x^2-16} = \frac{2(-x/4)}{1-(-x/4)^2} = \tan(2\alpha)\text{ where } \tan\alpha = \frac{-x}{4}. 
R\sin A=x^2-16
R\cos A=8x\implies R=x^2+16
\cos A=\frac{8x}{x^2+16}
(x^2-16)\sin x+8x\cos x
=(x^2+16)(\cos A \cos x+\sin A\sin x)
=(x^2+16)\cos (x-A)
=(x^2+16)\cos(x-\cos^{-1}(\frac{8x}{x^2+16}))
y=x-\cos^{-1}(\frac{8x}{x^2+16})
\frac{dy}{dx}=\frac{x^2+8}{x^+16}
\int\frac{x^2+8}{(x^2-16)\sin (x) + 8 x \cos(x)} \ dx
=\int\frac{x^2+8}{(x^2-16)\cos(x-\cos^{-1}(\frac{8x}{x^2+16}))} \ dx
=\int\frac{dy}{\mathrm{cos}y}=\int \sec ydy=\ln|\sec y+ \tan y|+C=\ln\tan (\frac{\pi}{4}+\frac{y}{2})+C
2B=\cos^{-1}(\frac{8x}{x^2+16}),\frac{8x}{x^2+16}=\cos2B
=\frac{1-\tan^2B}{1+\tan^2B}\implies \tan^2B=(\frac{4+x}{4-x})^2
y=x-2\tan^{-1}(\frac{4+x}{4-x})=x-2(\frac{\pi}{4}+\tan^{-1}(\frac{x}{4})) 
x=\frac{\pi}{2}, y=-2\tan^{-1}\frac{\pi}{8}
x=\frac{\pi}{4}, y=-\frac{\pi}{4}-2\tan^{-1}\frac{\pi}{16}
